<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12204d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12204d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12204d"> 204(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 1 dog&apos;s flesh / 2 cook pregn / 3 bastard&apos;s dish</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Allusion aux interdictions d&apos;ordre magico-religieux auxquelles &eacute;taient soumis les trois fr&egrave;res: le premier ne devait pas manger de la chair de chien, ni le second d&apos;un plat pr&eacute;par&eacute; par une femme enceinte, ni le troisi&egrave;me d&apos;aliments offert par un b&acirc;tard. <br><font color="green">[Allusion to the magic-religious taboos which the three brothers had to obey: the first was that you should not eat the meat of a dog, the second not to eat a meal prepart\ed by a pregnant woman and the third not to eat food offered by a bastard.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 30n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
